        <Parent_String>rail transit systems [300155844], public transit by form [300155843], public transit (infrastructure) [300155835], transit systems (infrastructure) [300008556], infrastructural systems [300155846], systems by function [300242038], systems (equipment) [300008550], Object Groupings and Systems (hierarchy name) [300241489], Objects Facet [300264092]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Designates rail systems operating on private but not necessarily exclusive right of way, at street level or grade separated, generally on electric power, at medium speeds (10-30 miles per hour), and generally making frequent stops at low platforms or directly at grade-level stations.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Designa sistemas de rieles operativos con derecho reservado de vía pero no necesariamente exclusivo, en el nivel de la calle o a un nivel separado, generalmente de energía eléctrica, a velocidades medias (10 - 30 mph), y generalmente haciendo paradas frecuentes en plataformas bajas o directamente en estaciones con nivel separado.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Aanduiding voor spoorsystemen op een eigen traject maar die wel rekening moeten houden met ander verkeer, gelegen op straatniveau of een eigen niveau, die meestal elektrisch worden voortbewogen met gemiddeld snelheden (15 tot 45 km per uur) en meestal met veel haltes hebben aan lage perrons of gelijkvloerse haltes.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>有自己專用道路的軌道系統，但不一定與其他車輛完全隔離，在一般路面上行駛或是分層行駛。通常以電力驅動，中速行駛（每小時10到30英里），一般在低月台或直接在地面車站多站停靠。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
